    • Method Detail

      • initializeTapeWithData

        public void initializeTapeWithData(java.util.ArrayList<T> data,
                          int position)
        Initializes the Tape with the given data. For each entry in parameter data a cell is written and the tape is moved to the right. After writing the data, the head is put into the given position.

      • initializeTapeWithData

        public void initializeTapeWithData(T[] data,
                          int position)
        Initializes the Tape with the given data. For each entry in parameter data a cell is written and the tape is moved to the right. After writing the data, the head is put into the given position.

      • move

        public void move(Direction direction)
        Moves the Head of the Tape in the given direction by 1 cell. Also creates empty cells with content null if the Head moves to a new position it's never been before. Notifies the listeners that the tape has been moved and, if it happened, that the tape has been expanded in size.

      • read

        public T read()
        Reads the data of the position where the head is currently located.
        Returns:
        The data in that position, or null if the header is at an invalid position

      • getContents

        public java.util.List<T> getContents()
        Returns:
        All the data from this Tape including empty cells. This List is unmodifiable.

      • getPosition

        public int getPosition()
        Returns:
        The current position of the head

      • write

        public void write(T content)
        Writes the given data onto the tape at the current position of the head. Any existing data will be overwritten. Notifies the listeners that data has been written.

      • addListener

        public void addListener(TapeChangeListener<T> listener)
        Adds the given listener to the list of listeners that will be notified according to the TapeChangeListener Interface. If the listener already is in the list, it will not be added again.

      • getCurrent

        public java.lang.String getCurrent()
        Returns:
        The String representation of the data in the cell the head is currently at. If a cell is empty(null) an underscore will be returned ("_")

      • getLeft

        public java.lang.String getLeft()
        Returns:
        The data of the Tape to the left of the head, exluding the cell the head is currently at. Also removes any empty cells from the leftmost cell up to and excluding the first non-empty cell or the current head position.

      • getRight

        public java.lang.String getRight()
        Returns:
        The data of the Tape to the right of the head, excluding the cell the head is currently at. Also removes any empty cells from the rightmost cell down to and excluding the last non-empty cell or the current head position.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        The String representation of all the data in the tape. Empty cells are represented by a "_". Also removes any empty cells from the edges.

      • stripEmptyLeft

        int stripEmptyLeft(int position)
        Removes every empty cell starting at the leftmost cell up to and excluding the first non-empty cell or the given position.

      • stripEmptyRight

        int stripEmptyRight(int position)
        Removes every empty cell starting at the rightmost cell up to and excluding the first non-empty cell or the given position

      • getDataFromTo

        private java.lang.String getDataFromTo(int startPos,
                             int endPos,
                             java.lang.String empty)
        Parameters:
        startPos - The first position to get
        endPos - The last position to get
        empty - is used as the string representation for empty cells
        Returns:
        A String containing the string representations of all the cells between and including startPos to endPos. For any empty cell the parameter empty is used as the String representation.

      • getDataAtPos

                            java.lang.String empty)
        Gets the string representation of a single cell. Empty cells are represented with the parameter empty
        Parameters:
